usage: validate_humanize_candidate_queue.py [-h] [--catalog CATALOG]
                                            [--queue-dir QUEUE_DIR]
                                            [--allowed-root ALLOWED_ROOT]
                                            [--format {json,text}]
                                            candidate

Validate a source-action-bound rewrite candidate without exporting corpus
prose. This is a publication gate for a *candidate package*, not a text
generator and not an academic-correctness checker. It proves only mechanical
facts: the selected action cards are available for the declared scene,
declared anchors survive in the candidate, existing invariant/style gates
pass, and the rewrite does not copy a long Chinese run from the action-card
source ranges or retain a known automatic template. Claims, evidence roles,
and causal explanations remain explicitly outside automatic verification.

positional arguments:
  candidate             candidate package JSON

options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --catalog CATALOG
  --queue-dir QUEUE_DIR
                        write candidate/result into accepted or rejected
  --allowed-root ALLOWED_ROOT
                        optional root containing candidate, before, and after
                        files
  --format {json,text}
